09/12/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Albanians marked on Wednesday (December 8th) 20 years since the day democracy replaced one of the toughest communism regimes in Europe.
Prime Minister Sali Berisha addressed the nation with a letter, congratulating leaders of the student movement for restoring human dignity to Albanian citizens on December 8th 1990.
"The European future of the country is owed to the freedom of the December 1990 students," he added.
December 8th is National Youth Day in Albania.
(Shekulli, NOA, Telegrafi, Top Channel, Balkan Web - 09/12/10)
